VIRGIN AMERICA ETOPS GATE TO GATE CHECKLIST
Pre-Departure
(PF/PM) Flight Release
• Review Flight Release as necessary to include EEP, ETP (CP1), EXP, MEL's, Volcanic Ash Report, etc.
• Designate Master.
(PM) Plotting Chart
• Plot EEP, ETP (CP1), EXP and any unnamed waypoints.
• Draw a course-line between any waypoints which are not on a published track.
(CA) ETOPS Flight Envelope, Position Report Guide, Gate-to-Gate Checklist, verify on-board.
Flight Deck Preparation
Verify "ETOPS" placard installed on the Forward Instrument Panel.
PF/PM) Aircraft Maintenance Logbook
• Verify ETOPS Logbook with blue pages, "ETOPS" watermark and applicable tail number.
• Verify ETOPS Pre-Departure Service Check (ETOPS PDSC).
NOTE: The aircraft must commence pushback prior to the "valid till" time which is annotated in the
"Resolution or Defer" block of the Aircraft Maintenance Logbook. Pushback is defined as the "out time"
from the AOC 000I STATUS page.
(PM) CPDLC Message Erase
• Erase all previous CPDLC messages. (ATC COM/ATC MENU 1 of 2/<MSG RECORD [4L]/*MSG RECORD
ERASE [5L]/*ERASE MSG RECORD CONFIRM [5L])
(PF) IR Initialization
• Perform complete alignment.
- If the flaps are extended, refer to FCOM-PRO-NOR-SOP-06.
• During alignment, check aircraft position from INIT-A/IRS INIT [3R] and compare against JEP 10-9 page
(i.e. airport reference point or specific gate coordinates if available) for position accuracy.
• (PM) Aircraft Position
• Upon completion of alignment, verify and record aircraft position on Master OFP. (DATA/POSITION
MONITOR [1L] /MIX IRS [4L])
(PF) INIT-B page
• Enter from Flight Release the actual fuel value for "11 PCT" into "RTE RSV/%" [3L]. (i.e.2.8)
• Enter from Flight Release the actual fuel value for "FAR" into "FINAL TIME" [5L]. (i.e.2.5)
(PF/PM) Route Verification
• Accomplish SOP Route Verification per FCOM-PRO-NOR-SOP-06.
• The PF will signify confirmation by circling each Class II waypoint verified on the Navigation Log.
NOTE: After the Oceanic Clearance has been received, entered and checked, no alterations or changes
should be made to the Primary Flight Plan.
• In order to display EEP, ETP(CP), EXP on the Navigation Displays (NDs) create "NEW WAYPOINT":
- Name each waypoint in the IDENT field of the NEW WAYPOINT page as "EEP", "CP1" and "EXP".
(DATA/DATA INDEX 2 of 2/STORED WAYPOINTS [1R]/NEW WAYPOINT-STORE [6R]/STORED WAYPOINT
1 of 1-NEW WAYPOINT> [5R] as required)
- Insert the applicable coordinates in the LAT/LONG [2L] field of the NEW WAYPOINT pages and then
STORE each new waypoint. [6R]
• To display each waypoint on the ND, insert the applicable waypoint in the "FIX INFO" pages. (F-PLN,
[1L], FIX INFO [1R], REF FIX 1-4)
CAUTION: It is not permissible to insert any additional waypoints including ETOPS; EEP, ETP (CP), EXP
into the actual flight plan as the waypoint is not part of the ATC F-PLN and would corrupt CPDLC/ADS-C
position reporting and any input error in coordinates may cause a track deviation.
Revision Date 20160129
